# Docker build context for deploy/colima's nginx image (see
# deploy/colima/Dockerfile) only ever reads frontend/dist/ and
# deploy/colima/nginx.conf -- nothing else in the repo is needed at build
# time. Without this file the entire repo, including backend/.venv
# (~1.6GB) and backend/storage's growing video/frame cache, was being sent
# to the Docker daemon on every single build (~530MB and climbing) -- which
# is also most of why an existing build-cache bug (a `COPY frontend/dist/`
# layer silently reusing a week-old cached layer instead of picking up a
# fresh build) went unnoticed for so long: a build that slow doesn't get
# re-run casually just to double-check.

.git/
backend/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/src/
.claude/
.agents/
*.md
repomix-output.xml
skills-lock.json
